---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Data Scientists | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Data Scientists working internationally, covering data science positions abroad, machine learning careers, and global analytics opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Data Scientists";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Data Scientists working abroad, analyzing data internationally, and pursuing careers across tech companies, research institutions, and enterprises worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/data-scientist-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/data-scientist-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Data Science Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Data Scientists extract insights from data using statistics, machine learning, and programming. International data science careers offer opportunities to work with global datasets, join leading tech companies worldwide, and contribute to cutting-edge analytics projects.
      </p>
      <p>
        International data science opportunities exist through multinational tech companies, global enterprises building data capabilities, research institutions, startups worldwide, and the highly portable nature of data skills that transfer across borders.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Data Scientists working abroad across tech companies, research institutions, and enterprises worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Data Scientists</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Intensive computer work', typical: 'Consider for profession' },
          { need: 'Eye coverage', why: 'Screen-heavy work', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Demanding work environment', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Preventive care', why: 'Sedentary lifestyle concerns', typical: 'Usually included' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Conference and onsite travel', typical: 'Often provided' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Tech Company Benefits</h3>
      <p>
        Data scientists typically work for tech companies or enterprises that provide comprehensive benefits. Major tech employers often offer premium health coverage including mental health support, wellness programs, and extensive preventive care. Startup benefits may be more variable.
      </p>
      <p>
        International positions at major companies often include relocation support and comprehensive coverage. Contract and freelance data science work requires self-arranged coverage but is less common in this field.
      </p>

      <h3>Sedentary Work Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Data science involves intensive computer work—coding, analysis, and visualization. Extended sitting, screen time, and focused mental work create ergonomic and eye strain concerns. Coverage addressing these sedentary work conditions supports career longevity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Tech Company</h3>
      <p>
        Major tech employer. Comprehensive benefits typically. Competitive packages. Tech offers premium coverage.
      </p>

      <h3>Enterprise</h3>
      <p>
        Large corporation data team. Corporate benefits standard. Established programs. Enterprise offers stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Startup</h3>
      <p>
        Growth-stage company. Benefits variable. Equity compensation. Startups offer opportunity.
      </p>

      <h3>Research Institution</h3>
      <p>
        Academic or research focus. Institutional benefits. Research environment. Institutions offer depth.
      </p>

      <h3>Consulting</h3>
      <p>
        Data science consultancy. Firm benefits typical. Client variety. Consulting offers diversity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Data Scientists"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Data Scientists working abroad across tech companies, research institutions, and enterprises worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Data Science Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Advanced Degree</h3>
      <p>
        Master's or PhD common. Statistics, CS, or related field. Quantitative training. Degree opens doors.
      </p>

      <h3>Technical Skills</h3>
      <p>
        Python, R, SQL proficiency. Machine learning frameworks. Statistical methods. Skills demonstrate capability.
      </p>

      <h3>Domain Knowledge</h3>
      <p>
        Industry-specific expertise. Business understanding. Problem context. Domain adds value.
      </p>

      <h3>Portfolio</h3>
      <p>
        Project demonstrations. GitHub presence. Published work. Portfolio shows competence.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Ergonomic</h3>
      <p>
        Extended computer work. Desk posture. Sedentary hours. Ergonomic coverage valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Eye Strain</h3>
      <p>
        Screen-intensive analysis. Code review. Visualization work. Eye coverage important.
      </p>

      <h3>Mental Health</h3>
      <p>
        Deadline pressure. Complex problem-solving. Project demands. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Repetitive Strain</h3>
      <p>
        Keyboard and mouse intensive. Coding hours. Analysis work. RSI coverage consideration.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Analysis</h3>
      <p>
        Data exploration. Statistical modeling. Pattern discovery. Analysis drives insights.
      </p>

      <h3>Modeling</h3>
      <p>
        Machine learning development. Algorithm selection. Model training. Modeling creates value.
      </p>

      <h3>Communication</h3>
      <p>
        Insights presentation. Stakeholder explanation. Data storytelling. Communication enables action.
      </p>

      <h3>Collaboration</h3>
      <p>
        Cross-functional work. Engineering partnership. Business alignment. Collaboration multiplies impact.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Data science skills highly sought. Worldwide opportunities. Competitive compensation. Demand strong.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Senior data scientist. ML engineer. Data science manager. Chief data officer. Multiple progressions.
      </p>

      <h3>Remote Potential</h3>
      <p>
        Remote work common. Location flexibility. Digital collaboration. Remote widely accepted.
      </p>

      <h3>Compensation</h3>
      <p>
        Premium salaries typical. Benefits competitive. Equity common. Compensation attractive.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a data scientist considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Tech companies typically provide comprehensive benefits. Verify coverage details before accepting. Premium packages common at major employers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do tech companies provide health coverage internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Major tech companies yes. Often comprehensive packages. May include relocation support. Verify specific offer terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is mental health coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for demanding work. Project pressure. Tech often includes. Ensure adequate coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Can I work remotely internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Increasingly common. Company policies vary. Tax and visa considerations. Remote potential high.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about ergonomic coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Important for computer-intensive work. Back and wrist concerns. Long-term consideration. Include in planning.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Strong demand continuing. AI field growing. Global opportunities. Outlook excellent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by reviewing employer benefits packages carefully. Ensure coverage addresses sedentary work concerns. Consider mental health support for demanding work. Verify international coverage scope for relocation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Data Scientists drive decision-making with analytics worldwide. Your coverage should support data science careers—addressing computer-intensive work, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across data work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Data Science Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Data Scientists working abroad across tech companies, research institutions, and enterprises worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
